Package: ros-groovy-hrpsys-ros-bridge
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, python-psutil, ros-groovy-actionlib, ros-groovy-camera-info-manager, ros-groovy-collada-urdf, ros-groovy-control-msgs, ros-groovy-diagnostic-aggregator, ros-groovy-diagnostic-msgs, ros-groovy-dynamic-reconfigure, ros-groovy-hrpsys, ros-groovy-hrpsys-tools, ros-groovy-image-transport, ros-groovy-robot-state-publisher, ros-groovy-roscpp, ros-groovy-rosnode, ros-groovy-rostest, ros-groovy-rqt-gui, ros-groovy-rqt-gui-py, ros-groovy-rqt-robot-dashboard, ros-groovy-rqt-robot-monitor, ros-groovy-rtmbuild, ros-groovy-sensor-msgs, ros-groovy-tf, ros-groovy-visualization-msgs
Description: hrpsys_ros_bridge package provides basic functionalities to bind hrpsys, a OpenRTM-based controller, and ROS. By using this package, you can write your ROS packages that communicate with your non-ROS robots that run on hrpsys. For communicating with the robots that run on OpenRTM without hrpsys, you can use openrtm_ros_bridge package.
